 {"id":"franken_networkx-egoedgeord","title":"REVIEW: [MEDIUM] ego_graph re-orients edges with ego node first (diverges from nx)","description":"fnx.ego_graph(G, n, radius=1) on fnx.path_graph(5) produced edges [(2, 1), (2, 3)] while nx produced [(1, 2), (2, 3)]. The Rust fast-path '_fnx.ego_graph_rust' re-orients every edge with the ego node as the first endpoint, losing the input graph's edge orientation. Reworked the Python wrapper to always compute the node set in Python (BFS/dijkstra) and copy edges from G in original insertion order — no more Rust fast-path for this function.","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-24T11:18:58.000000000Z","created_by":"cc-networkx","updated_at":"2026-04-24T11:18:58.000000000Z","closed_at":"2026-04-24T11:18:58.000000000Z","close_reason":"Always use Python path; preserve G's edge orientation","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"franken_networkx-assortkw","title":"REVIEW: [MEDIUM] degree_assortativity_coefficient missing x/y/weight/nodes kwargs","description":"nx.degree_assortativity_coefficient(G, x='out', y='in', weight=None, nodes=None) — fnx's Rust binding exposed only (g). Users passing weight= or x=/y= variants TypeError'd. Added a Python wrapper that delegates to nx for any non-default kwarg while keeping the Rust fast-path for the plain default call. Verified weighted / in-out / nodes-filter all match nx.","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-24T11:21:15.000000000Z","created_by":"cc-networkx","updated_at":"2026-04-24T11:21:15.000000000Z","closed_at":"2026-04-24T11:21:15.000000000Z","close_reason":"Python wrapper delegates to nx for non-default kwargs","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"franken_networkx-effkw","title":"REVIEW: [LOW] efficiency / global_efficiency / local_efficiency used 'g' instead of 'G'","description":"Kwarg-style drop-in calls fnx.global_efficiency(G=graph) TypeError'd because the Rust binding named the param 'g'. Wrapped in thin Python shims with G as first param.","status":"closed","priority":4,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-24T11:21:15.000000000Z","created_by":"cc-networkx","updated_at":"2026-04-24T11:21:15.000000000Z","closed_at":"2026-04-24T11:21:15.000000000Z","close_reason":"Python wrappers","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
-{"id":"franken_networkx-copyedgeord","title":"REVIEW: [MEDIUM] Graph(fnx_src) / G.copy() / G.to_undirected() reverse edge orientation","description":"fnx.Graph(src).copy() on src = Graph with edges [(0,1),(1,2)] yields [(0,1),(2,1)] — the second edge reversed. Similarly G.copy(as_view=False) and G.to_undirected(as_view=False) emit edges in canonical-smallest-endpoint-first sometimes and reversed other times, diverging from nx which preserves original insertion order. Pre-existing Rust-side bug surfaced after rebuild. Needs a Rust-side fix in the constructor/copy paths. Queued.","status":"open","priority":3,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-24T11:21:15.000000000Z","created_by":"cc-networkx","updated_at":"2026-04-24T11:21:15.000000000Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"franken_networkx-copyedgeord","title":"REVIEW: [MEDIUM] Graph(fnx_src) / G.copy() / G.to_undirected() reverse edge orientation","description":"fnx.Graph(src).copy() on src = Graph with edges [(0,1),(1,2)] yields [(0,1),(2,1)] — the second edge reversed. Similarly G.copy(as_view=False) and G.to_undirected(as_view=False) emit edges in canonical-smallest-endpoint-first sometimes and reversed other times, diverging from nx which preserves original insertion order. Pre-existing Rust-side bug surfaced after rebuild. Needs a Rust-side fix in the constructor/copy paths. Queued.","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-24T11:21:15.000000000Z","created_by":"cc-networkx","updated_at":"2026-04-24T11:30:09.555754848Z","closed_at":"2026-04-24T11:30:09.555754848Z","close_reason":"Rebuilt constructor, copy, and to_undirected paths from public edge iteration order","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
